# Step-4 Directive 1 — build context for the backend production images.
#
# Keep the context lean (the Nx monorepo is large) and — critically — keep
# secrets/build-output OUT of every image layer. The builder stage runs
# `npm ci` + `npm run prisma:generate` + `nx build`, so SOURCE, prisma SCHEMAS,
# nx config and tools/ MUST stay in context; only host-side artifacts and
# secrets are excluded here.

# --- Never ship secrets (assert: no .env / keys in any layer) ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# --- Host-side install/build artifacts (the image rebuilds these itself) ---
node_modules
**/node_modules
dist
build
out-tsc
tmp
.nx/cache
.nx/workspace-data

# Per-module Prisma clients are regenerated INSIDE the builder (WASM engine,
# deterministic) — never copy the host's generated output into the context.
**/prisma/generated
**/.prisma

# --- VCS / CI / editor / OS noise ---
.git
.github
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
*.swp

# --- Tests, coverage, e2e + local-dev runtime state (not needed to build/run) ---
coverage
**/coverage
.local-stack
test-results
**/test-results
playwright-report
**/playwright-report
playwright/.cache
**/playwright/.cache
pact/logs
pact/pacts
scratch
doc/prompts

# --- Infra/docs not consumed by the app build ---
infrastructure
openapi
doc
*.md
!README.md

# Don't recurse Docker artifacts into the context
Dockerfile
**/Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose*.yml
